<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Selling in Acacia Ridge requires positioning the property accurately within the southern corridor. Buyers here are comparing value across Moorooka, Salisbury, Coopers Plains and Rocklea simultaneously, which means pricing needs to be grounded in the most current comparable data rather than broad suburb median figures. The right buyer profile and the right campaign strategy can make a substantial difference to the final result.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The Logan Motorway interchange at the suburb's southern boundary provides direct access to the Gateway Motorway and the Pacific Motorway network, making Acacia Ridge a practical choice for buyers who work across multiple parts of Brisbane. The residential streets north of Beaudesert Road, particularly those on the Moorooka and Salisbury boundary, attract the owner-occupier segment that sets the upper end of the market. Investor demand from buyers targeting strong rental yields relative to purchase price has been consistent across economic cycles. Acacia Ridge State School is the primary school anchor for the residential catchment.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229;">
