    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Acacia Ridge?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Block size, proximity to the residential core away from industrial areas, and condition are the key value drivers. Affordability relative to neighbours and exceptional motorway access attract both investors and first home buyers. Homes on quieter residential streets consistently outperform those adjacent to industrial precincts.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Acacia Ridge?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Acacia Ridge homes typically sell within 25 to 40 days. The suburb draws a dual buyer pool of investors seeking rental yields and first home buyers priced out of neighbouring Salisbury and Moorooka. Correct pricing is essential as buyers are actively comparing value across the southern corridor.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Acacia Ridge?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Acacia Ridge is a practical, well-connected suburb. The Logan and Pacific motorways are easily accessible, with Salisbury and Coopers Plains train stations within reach. The residential streets north of Beaudesert Road have a genuine neighbourhood feel that is separate from the industrial activity in the suburb's southern section.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Acacia Ridge a good suburb to sell in?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Acacia Ridge attracts consistent investor and first home buyer demand. As Moorooka and Salisbury have repriced, buyer attention has moved further south and Acacia Ridge has benefited from that migration. Its affordability and motorway connectivity sustain interest across market cycles.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

